The '''Embassy of Montenegro in Washington, D.C.''' is the [[diplomatic mission]] of [[Montenegro]] to the [[United States]]. The embassy is located at 1610 [[New Hampshire Avenue]], [[Northwest, Washington, D.C.]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mvp.gov.me/en/sections/Missions/Embassies-and-consulates-of-Montenegro/united-states-of-america|title=United States of America|website=www.mvp.gov.me|access-date=2018-01-17}}</ref><ref><nowiki>http://embassy-finder.com/montenegro_in_washington_usa</nowiki></ref> The embassy is also accredited on a non-resident basis to Canada and Mexico.<ref>http://www.mvp.gov.me/en/sections/Missions/Embassies-and-consulates-of-Montenegro/Cuba</ref>

The current Ambassador of Montenegro to the United States is Mr. [[Nebojša Kaluđerović]].<ref>[[Nebojša Kaluđerović]]</ref>

There is one [[Consulate General]] in [[New York City]] (Consul General Branko Milić).

Montenegro's Permanent Mission to the [[United Nations]] in New York is led by Ambassador [[Zeljko Perovic]].

