The '''National Library of Togo''' (''Bibliothèque nationale du Togo'') is the national [[library]] of [[Togo]] and is located in the capital, [[Lomé]]. It was founded in 1969. In the late 1990s, the National Library in Lomé acquired a collection of approximately 18,000 volumes.<ref>[http://www.nationsencyclopedia.com/Africa/Togo.html Nation encyclopedia]</ref><ref>[http://www.uneca.org/Library/Library_associations.htm List of Addresses of the Major Libraries in Africa] ({{webarchive |url=https://www.webcitation.org/6BPJcaGdn?url=http://www.uneca.org/Library/Library_associations.htm |date=October 14, 2012 }})</ref>

