{{Politics of Poland}}

The '''Public Prosecutor General''' ({{lang-pl|Prokurator Generalny}}) is the top [[prosecutor|prosecuting]] officer in [[Poland]]. Until 2010 and from 2016 the office was combined with the Polish [[Ministry of Justice of the Republic of Poland|Minister of Justice]]. [[Zbigniew Ziobro]] is current Public Prosecutor General of [[Poland]].

